fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.data.types

Interface IDateTimeData

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IData<IDateTimeType>, ITimeStructure

    public interface IDateTimeData
extends IData<IDateTimeType>, ITimeStructure
    Provides typed access to date with time data for a cell. Values should be exchanged with the connector in the UTC time zone.

    The data value is of type Date. The value may be set using Date or Long.

    Note: the UTC time zone is used when getting and setting the time-of-day fields (hours, minutes...).

    Thread-safety: implementations of this interface are not required to be safe for concurrent access. Therefore, processing should generally not be shared between multiple threads.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies

      • getMsecDateTimeValue

        long getMsecDateTimeValue()
        Gets the date-with-time value as a number of milliseconds relative to the Unix Epoch time. The time of day is inherently relative to the UTC timezone.

        Note: NULL values are coerced to 0.

        Returns:
        true if the value is true, or false if the value is false or null.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        getValue()

      • setMsecDateTimeValue

        void setMsecDateTimeValue(long value)
        Sets the date-with-time value as a number of milliseconds relative to the Unix Epoch time.

        Note: you cannot set a NULL value using this method. Use setValue instead.

        Parameters:
        value - value to set, as a number of milliseconds relative to the Unix Epoch time. Any milliseconds for the time of day are inherently relative to the UTC timezone.
        Since:
        1.0
